    <text>
        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>&#34;Jerusalem &#40;Holy City&#41; the Glory of all Lands.&#34;<lb/>
                ALFRED A. MARCUS&#44;<lb/>
                Diamond Merchant and Importer&#44;<lb/>
                Purchaser of Real Estate&#44; &#40;Landed Property.&#41;<lb/>
                Residence&#44; 127 DARTMOUTH STREET.<lb/></p>
            <p>No business will be transacted or interviews had on the Jewish Sabbath&#44; from one hour before sunset on<lb/> Friday until one hour after sunset on Saturday&#44; or on the Jewish Festivals&#44; and no letters will be opened on<lb/> those days.<lb/></p>
            <p>Boston&#44; Tishri 28 AM. 5643<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi> Mr. S. Morais<lb/>
                My very dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p><sic>Your&#39;s</sic> of the 25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> recd. should<lb/> not have sent the postal regarding the Album<lb/> but Adam&#39;s Express notified me I had not<lb/> <sic>address</sic> it properly hence my card.  As I<lb/> before stated never thank me or my family<lb/> for such trifles we send&#44; it is our most<lb/> heavenly father who prompts all hearts<lb/> &#38; we all consider you so richly deserve<lb/> our tokens of friendship&#44; for your holy<lb/> Zeal in Israels cause.  I have so much<lb/> daily experience of the gross ingratitude<lb/> of so called Chasan&#39;s&#44; &#38; Ministers when<lb/> we do find one so rich in God&#39;s love the<lb/> little I can do I feel but too happy.<lb/>  On the 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. day of Heshvan Sabbath a<lb/> week our patriarch &#38; mutual friend with<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
                <p>God Blessing will be ninety eight years<lb/> please write a few lines of congratulations<lb/> to him.<lb/></p>
                <p>My Succoth never looked so handsome<lb/> as it did this year&#44; &#38; altho I had all<lb/> my rich painting there was not a single<lb/> article damaged altho one day it poured<lb/> in torrents&#44; it was visited by immense<lb/> crowds of all denominations&#44; you can<lb/> form no idea with what veneration the<lb/> citizens of this City regarded the Succoth<lb/> &#38; all its teachings&#44; far more than even<lb/> our own people I recd. a very nice letter<lb/> from President Arthur &#38; he felt extremely<lb/> sorry his engagements at the Capital prevented<lb/> his presence.<lb/></p>
                <p>With the most sincere regards in which<lb/> Mrs. Marcus &#38; family join to you &#38; all yours<lb/> God Bless you remain as ever<lb/> Yours most faithfully<lb/> Alfred A Marcus<lb/></p>
                
                <p>I have placed the<lb/> &#91;&#63;&#93; which I bought of your friend in Philadelphia<lb/> in our Holy Ark &#38; it <sic>look</sic> very nice&#44; &#38; the<lb/> inscription is also touching to all with the hands<lb/> spread blessing I hope all Israel.<lb/></p>
        </body>
